  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Notably, SafetyBench (Zhang et al., 2023a) and SuperCLUE-Safety (Xu et al., 2023a) evaluated LLMs with multiple-choice or open-ended questions covering various safety concerns.",
    "In addition to evaluation, LLM-based monitors (Inan et al., 2023; Zhang et al., 2024) are developed to moderate LLM-generated content.",
    "However, benchmark questions can not expose behavioral risks in interactive environments, and thus struggle to provide a practical safety evaluation for LLM agents.",
    "Moreover, whether content monitors are able to function in open-agent scenarios is still a question.",
    "To tackle the aforementioned challenge, few studies have investigated safety risks in applications of LLM agents."
  ],
